The World Health Organization estimates that between five and 10 percent of us
suffer from depression at any given time. But fewer than a third of those with
depression receive appropriate care. In the United States, more than 21 million
people suffer from depression. For millions, no treatment works. Now, doctors
are trying an experimental technique that shows promise in treating some
difficult cases of depression. VOA's Carol Pearson reports.
 
 
 
 
